Author: Matthew Benak, Kathryn Nichols
Date: May 16, 2013
Source a: Wayne Suttles. 2004. Musqueam Reference Grammar. UBC Press.

# 'The Deer Drive' #

#1
Source: a:524
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {}
nemʔ ct xᵂaʔaθ nemʔ ʔə ƛ! Halfway
nemʔ c-t xᵂaʔaθ nemʔ ʔə ƛ! Halfway
go AUX-1PSUBJ deer.drive go OBL ART Halfway
We are going on a deer drive at Halfway.

#2
Source: a:524
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {}
ʔəpelə ct ceʔ wənit hayeʔ 
ʔəpənelə c-t ceʔ wə-niʔ-t hayeʔ
ten.people AUX-1PSUBJ FUT when-be.there-1PLSUBJ leave.
There will be ten of us when we leave.  

#3
Source: a:524
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {}
nemʔ ct wekənaɬ 
nemʔ c-t wekən-aɬ 
go AUX-1PSUBJ wagon-by
We'll go by wagon.

#4 OK
Source: a:524
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {}
sq!əlim ct ceʔ 
sq!əlim c-t ceʔ 
camped.out AUX-1PSUBJ FUT
We'll be camped out.

#5
Source: a:525
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {}
χəθilə ceʔ kᵂθə sqᵂ!aqᵂ!əɬ 
χəʔaθənelə ceʔ kᵂθə sqᵂ!aqᵂ!əɬ
four.persons FUT DET(MN) lying.in.wait
Four will be lying in wait. 

#6
Source: a:525
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {}
ƛ!a ceʔ kᵂələxt kᵂθə sməyəθ wəmʔis ceʔ wəɬcɬaqᵂθət
ƛ!a ceʔ kᵂələx-ət kᵂθə sməyəθ wə-mʔi-əs ceʔ wəɬ-cɬaqᵂ-θət
BE3P FUT shoot-TR DET(MN) deer when-come-3SUBSUBJ FUT already-pass.through-REFL
They will be the ones who will shoot the deer when they start coming through.

#7
Source: a:525
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {}
i ƛ!a ceʔ kᵂə tə səwʔawləsalɬ nemʔ nəsq!aʔ kᵂ!əns nemʔ xᵂaʔaθ yəq!ewʔəm ceʔ ʔeɬtən steʔe ʔə kᵂ! stəqeye 
ʔəyʔ ƛ!a ceʔ tə səwʔawləsalɬ nemʔ nə-sq!aʔ kᵂ!ə nə-s-nemʔ xᵂaʔaθ yə-q!ewʔəm ceʔ ʔeɬtən steʔe ʔə kᵂ!ə stəqeye 
and BE3P FUT DET(MN) youths go 1POSS-company DET(MR) 1NOMSUBJ-NOM-go deer.drive along-howl FUT 3PL like OBL DET(MR) wolf
And then it will be the boys who go with me when I got to drive the deer, howling like wolves as they go along.

#8
Source: a:525
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {}
ƛ!a ceʔ səw yətatəsəts kᵂə sment ʔeɬtən wəmʔis wəɬweɬətəs kᵂθə sməyəθ 
ƛ!a ceʔ s-wə-yə-PROG-təs-ət-s kᵂə sment ʔeɬtən wə-mʔi-əs PROG-weɬ-ət-əs kᵂθə sməyəθ
BE3P FUT NOM-EMPH-along-PROG-hit.together-TR-3NOMSUBJ DET(MN) stone 3PL when-come-3SUBSUBJ PROG-chase-TR-3SUBSUBJ DET(MN) deer
They'll be the ones striking stones together when they come chasing the deer.

#9 
Source: a:525
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {}
stqᵂ!iqən tə sment i ƛ!ew stətiqᵂ! tə stalʔəw
stqᵂ!iqən tə sment ʔəyʔ ƛ!ə wə-stətiqᵂ! tə stalʔəw
steep DET(MP) mountain and too EMPH-sheer DET(MP) river.
The mountainside is steep and also the river bank is sheer.


#10
Source: a:525
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {}
skᵂ!ey kᵂə snemʔs hilθət
skᵂ!ey kᵂə s-nemʔ-s hilθət
impossible DET(MR) NOM-go-3NOMSUBJ roll
They can't let themselves go.

#11
Source: a:525
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {}
wənʔan wəƛ!əp wənʔan wəcicəɬ   
wə-nʔan wə-ƛ!əp wə-nʔan wə-cicəɬ   
EMPH-too EMPH-deep EMPH-too EMPH-high
It is too far down and too far up.

#12
Source: a:525
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {}
ʔəwəteʔ kᵂə ʃxᵂnemʔs təwƛ!a sməyəθ 
ʔəwəteʔ kᵂə ʃxᵂ-nemʔ-s təwƛ!a sməyəθ 
none DET(MR) OBLNOM-go-3NOMSUBJ that deer
The deer have no place to go.

#13 
Source: a:526
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {}
nəw nemʔ ʔalʔ χᵂənxenəm təwƛ!a sməyəθ 
niʔ wə-nemʔ ʔalʔ χᵂənxenəm təwƛ!a sməyəθ 
be.there EMPH-go just run that deer
The deer can only run.

